    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I like to throw in a few beautiful bay leaves into my Black Bean soup. Tampa (where I dwell) is famous for it&#8217;s Cuban cuisine. I learned from an old Cuban woman that lots of Bay leaf is the secret. </>Mmmmmmm, wonderful, aromatic Black Bean soup with little bits of onion staring at you lovingly and a good dollop of sour cream. </>Heaven.</p>
    </div>

