  <li id="comment-9195" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/00700083683860123064" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Kawa</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/01/tomorrow-tomorrow/#comment-9195"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-05-20T15:38:12-04:00">Wednesday, May 20, 2009 at 3:38 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>These look great and tasty. Question: do you use canned black beans or black bean soup (in the red can, at least for Goya)? The soup version is already nicely spiced, fairly garlicy. A great way to doctor a can of black bean soup is to cook rice in it (as opposed to water or broth), adding water ONLY if necessary, and you get a lovely Cuban-style rice and beans dish called &#8216;Moro&#8217; that way.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
