      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/03307475669131944104" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Jenn</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/01/tomorrow-tomorrow/#comment-9198"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-05-04T00:08:15-04:00">Tuesday, May 4, 2010 at 12:08 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just made the black beans, with a few substitutions &#8212; instead of hot sauce, I used 1/4 tsp ground chipotle chili (a little smoky) and 1/4 tsp Old Bay Seasoning (I omitted the salt because Old Bay has salt), and 1/4 tsp garlic powder for the fresh garlic (since I have no garlic press, and also it seemed like the garlic would stay a bit raw).  Made brown rice, and a sliced tomato salad, and that&#39;s a very easy, quick, and tasty meal!  Thanks for sharing the recipe!</p>
    </div>

